- "constellation" refers to the groups to which these users belong;
- "contributions of light" refers to the number of submissions made by each user.

- 'digital garden of submissions' refers to the database of submissions and their histories;
- 'flowers' metaphorically represent the submissions;
- 'most recent approved flowers' refers to the latest approved submissions in the group;
- 'latest changes' refers to the most recent changes recorded in the submission history.

- "blossoms of approval" refers to approved submissions;
- "flowers that are in full bloom" refers to the approval rate, which is the ratio of approved submissions to the total number of submissions, expressed as a percentage;
- "garden of submissions" is a metaphor for the database containing the submissions.

- "vibrant flowers" refers to submissions that have been approved and have a high number of distinct tags and categories;
- "gardeners" refers to users who made the submissions;
- "messages" refers to notifications received by the users.

- 'saplings' refers to users in the database;
- 'blossomed' refers to users whose role is 'submitter';
- 'flowers' refers to submissions;
- 'pollinated' refers to submissions that have been approved;
- 'nectar' refers to the ratings of the submissions.

- "Prolific gardeners" refers to users who have more than 5 submissions;
- "Blossoms" refers to submissions;
- "Gardens" refers to groups;
- "Rank" is determined by the number of submissions within each group.

- 'blossoms' refer to submissions;
- 'marked with the seal of approval' means the submissions have been approved;
- 'gardeners of the Marketing Team' refers to users who belong to the 'Marketing Team' group.

- "submission" refers to a post or entry in a database;
- "waves of comments" refers to a high number of comments;
- "attracted" implies that the submission has received a significant amount of attention in the form of comments.

- 'approval rate' is the percentage of approved submissions out of the total submissions;
- 'review ratings' are numerical scores given by users to submissions;
- 'submission ID' uniquely identifies each submission in the database.
